text: The 2020 United States presidential election in Maine was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Former Vice President Joe Biden and his running mate U.S. SenatorKamala Harris had won 3 electoral votes in the Electoral College, while incumbent President Donald Trump and incumbent Vice President Mike Pence had won only 1 electoral vote. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:21st century in Maine
title: 2020 United States presidential election in Maine
